contentrichtext.text: {{Wiktionary|eg}} '''Eg''' may refer to: * e.g., an abbreviation of ''[[exempli gratia]]'', Latin: "for example" * [[Eg White]], a British musician, songwriter and producer. * [[Eg, Afghanistan]], a town * [[Eg River]], a river in northern Mongolia. * [[Exagram]], an SI unit of mass * [[band gap energy]] '''EG''' also stands for: * [[Evil Geniuses]], an electronic sports team * [[Eurographics]], European Association for Computer Graphics * EG, a model code for a 1992-95 [[Honda Civic]] & Civic Hatchback * [[EG (magazine)|''EG'' (magazine)]], a journal dedicated to chess endgame studies * [[E.G. Records]], a music record label * [[.eg]], Internet country code top-level domain for Egypt * [[Japan Asia Airways]], IATA code * [[Equatorial Guinea]], a small African country * [[Electric Gardens]], a music festival in Faversham, UK * [[Ethylene glycol]], an alcohol * [[Enskilda Gymnasiet]], a private secondary school in Stockholm, Sweden * eG, ''[[eingetragene Genossenschaft]]'', a registered cooperative society under German law == See also == * [[Egg (disambiguation)]] {{disambiguation}}
